 ANALYSTS at Vetiva Capital Management Limited have projected 8.6 percent growth banks’ lending in 2019. July 29, 2019 In "Business" A TOTAL of seven leading deposit money banks, DMBs, may now be under pressure to beef up their loan portfolio following a recent directive by the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN, which requires banks to give out 60 percent of their deposits as loans to the real sector. July 15, 2019 In "Business" In a bid to boost economic growth, the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), yesterday, mandated Deposit Money Banks, DMBs, to give out minimum of 60 percent of their deposits as loans with effect from September 2019. July 5, 2019 In "Business"